{
  "texts": [
    "41 proposed a deep learning method to accelerate the design and optimization of multivalent materials with fewer data and less domain-knowledge restriction.",
    "In addition, organic redox compounds are also potential candidates for rechargeable batteries for the rich in elements and structural diversity.",
    "42 employed ML to predict novel organic polymers with ideal redox potentials.",
    "43 collected one million molecules from PubChem and after four rounds of filtration based on unsupervised clustering and supervised regression, they identified 1524 molecules as potential organic electrode molecules.",
    "Finally, the optimization of the synthetic parameters 44 through ML models and microstructure determination 45 based on GAN are also essential research directions to discover advanced cathodes for high energy density batteries."
  ]
}